<paragraph id="8BCE36DAFFE3FFAB24FBFB22FBD5FA14" blockId="25.[151,1437,1205,1530]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">
<collectingCountry id="F366764AFFE3FFAB24FBFB22FF43FB21" box="[151,185,1205,1231]" name="American Samoa" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">As</collectingCountry>
stated by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE3FFAB2550FB22FCF1FB21" author="Welter-Schultes" box="[316,779,1205,1231]" pageId="25" pageNumber="46" refString="Welter-Schultes, F. W. &amp; Klug, R. (2009) Nomenclatural consequences resulting from the rediscovery of Les figures des plantes et animaux d'usage en medicine, a rare work published by Garsault in 1764, in the zoological literature. Bulletin of zoological Nomenclature, 66 (3), 225 - 241." type="journal article" year="2009">
Welter-Schultes &amp; Klug (
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB2611FB22FD38FB21" box="[637,706,1205,1231]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="2009.0">2009</number>
: 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB26A2FB22FCFBFB21" box="[718,769,1205,1231]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="234.0">234</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
, the plate 
<quantity id="4C899B3FFFE3FFAB27E2FB22FC24FB21" box="[910,990,1205,1231]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6967199999999998" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" unit="in" value="668.0">668 in</quantity>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE3FFAB278BFB22FB5AFB21" author="Garsault" box="[999,1184,1205,1231]" pageId="25" pageNumber="40" refString="Garsault, F. A. P. de (1764) Les Figures des plantes et animaux d'usage en medecine, decrits dans la Matiere Medicale de Mr. Geoffroy Medecin. Paris, [i - v] + 1 - 20, pl. 644 - 729." type="book chapter" year="1764">
Garsault, 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB200EFB22FB5AFB21" box="[1122,1184,1205,1231]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1764.0">1764</number>
</bibRefCitation>
shows the 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE3FFAB2143FB21FEFFFB1A" authority="Lacepède, 1788" authorityName="Lacepède" authorityYear="1788" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacertus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="terrestris">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE3FFAB2143FB21FEFFFB1A" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Lacertus terrestris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or “Lézard gris”, which is undoubtedly the species presently named 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE3FFAB2020FB4CFF1AFAF4" authority="Laurenti, 1768" authorityName="Laurenti" authorityYear="1768" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Podarcis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="muralis">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE3FFAB2020FB4CFAE6FB1A" box="[1100,1308,1243,1268]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Podarcis muralis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE3FFAB2141FB4DFF22FAF4" author="Laurenti" pageId="25" pageNumber="42" refString="Laurenti, J. N. (1768) Specimen medicum, exhibens synopsin Reptilium emendatam cum experimentis circa venena et antidota Reptilium austriacorum. Viennae, Joan. Thom. Nob. de Trattnern, i - ii + 1 - 215, pl. 1 - 5." type="book chapter" year="1768">
Laurenti, 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB24FBFA97FF22FAF4" box="[151,216,1280,1306]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1768.0">1768</number>
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, the “wall lizard” (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE3FFAB2596FA97FD64FAF4" author="Arnold" box="[506,670,1280,1306]" pageId="25" pageNumber="35" refString="Arnold, E. N. (1973) Relationships of the Palaearctic lizards assigned to the genera Lacerta, Algyroides and Psammodromus (Reptilia: Lacertidae). Bulletin of the British Museum of natural History, Zoology, 29, 289 - 366." type="journal article" year="1973">
Arnold, 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB260CFA97FD64FAF4" box="[608,670,1280,1306]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1973.0">1973</number>
</bibRefCitation>
) (family 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE3FFAB277DFA97FBB5FAF4" authority="Batsch, 1788" authorityName="Batsch" authorityYear="1788" box="[785,1103,1280,1306]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="family">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE3FFAB277DFA97FC59FAF7" box="[785,931,1280,1305]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">LACERTIDAE</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE3FFAB27C7FA97FBB5FAF4" author="Batsch" box="[939,1103,1280,1306]" pageId="25" pageNumber="36" refString="Batsch, A. J. G. C. (1788) Versuch einer Anleitung, zur Kennniss und Geschichte der Thiere und Mineralien. Erster Theil. Jena, Akademischen Buchhandlung, i - viii + 1 - 528, pl. 1 - 5." type="book chapter" year="1788">
Batsch, 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB2062FA97FBB5FAF4" box="[1038,1103,1280,1306]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1788.0">1788</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
). The latter specific nomen having been in wide and universal use (for a list of more than 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB27E0FAB2FC50FAD1" box="[908,938,1317,1343]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="25.0">25</number>
recent references, see e.g. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE3FFAB209EFAB2FEBAFA8A" author="Gruschwitz" pageId="25" pageNumber="41" refString="Gruschwitz, M. &amp; Bohme, W. (1986) Podarcis muralis (Laurenti, 1768) - Mauereidechse. In: W. Bohme (Ed.), Handbuch der Reptilien und Amphibien Europas, Band 2 / II, Wiesbaden, Aula-Verlag, 155 - 208." type="book chapter" year="1986">
Gruschwitz &amp; Böhme 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB2497FADDFEBAFA8A" box="[251,320,1354,1380]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1986.0">1986</number>
</bibRefCitation>
: 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB2521FADDFE44FA8A" box="[333,446,1354,1380]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="204.5" valueMax="208.0" valueMin="201.0">201–208</number>
) for more two centuries and Garsault’s nomen having been ignored since its description, the prevailing usage must be maintained according to Article 23.9. 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB200DFAE7FB91FA64" box="[1121,1131,1392,1418]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1.0">1</number>
of the 
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE3FFAB20AFFAE7FAF8FA67" box="[1219,1282,1392,1417]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Code</emphasis>
. The nomen 
<taxonomicName id="4C714D59FFE3FFAB24FBFA01FDB2FA41" authority="Garsault, 1764" authorityName="Garsault" authorityYear="1764" box="[151,584,1429,1455]" class="Reptilia" family="Lacertidae" genus="Lacertus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Squamata" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="terrestris">
<emphasis id="B905EAC8FFE3FFAB24FBFA01FE79FA41" box="[151,387,1430,1455]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">Lacertus terrestris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE04B2BFFE3FFAB25E0FA02FDB2FA41" author="Garsault" box="[396,584,1429,1455]" pageId="25" pageNumber="40" refString="Garsault, F. A. P. de (1764) Les Figures des plantes et animaux d'usage en medecine, decrits dans la Matiere Medicale de Mr. Geoffroy Medecin. Paris, [i - v] + 1 - 20, pl. 644 - 729." type="book chapter" year="1764">
Garsault, 
<number id="3DB924FDFFE3FFAB2665FA02FDB2FA41" box="[521,584,1429,1455]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26" value="1764.0">1764</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
remains however nomenclaturally available and could possibly be resurrected in the future, e.g. for a subspecies. This would require to designate a neophoront (
<typeStatus id="54CA8878FFE3FFAB20B5FA2DFAC3FA3A" box="[1241,1337,1466,1492]" pageId="25" pageNumber="26">neotype</typeStatus>
) for this nominal taxon, which should preferably have originated from the Paris region.
</paragraph>
